Tom &amp; DocDel,<br>
     Muchas Gracias!!  Yes, the rucksack gets a bit heavy these days, but it's due to things other than 'Nam; which probably don't belong on this site.  Like Anthony Newley in &quot;Stop the World! I want to get off.&quot;, it's easier said than done.  I just have to slow down enough to live my life, rather than have events run me.<br>
     Actually I was just trying to agree with Chet.  Looks like my underlying feelings were expressed more than I realized.  We'll keep on truckin'.  Am familiar with &quot;those miles to go before I sleep.&quot;                                                                                           Hey Doc Spatz,<br>
     Never met a Vietnam Vet yet who could be shut up by a memorial or anything else.  And I'm SHOCKED! SHOCKED! that there is no salvation through politics and politicians.  Remember that overused quote of Churchill's: &quot;Democracy is the worst form of government, except all the others.&quot;  For many, power is more seductive than money, and more than a few good men have become markedly less so after acquiring a taste for power.  The person who consciously sets about to do evil is rare, but the person who compromises himself bit by bit till he hardly realizes that he has lost his principles is all too common.<br>
     All of us fight this battle in our lives; though rarely for as high stakes as someone with responsibility for others' lives.  Hopefully, we win more than we lose, and when it counts.  I believe I wouldn't have lied to the American people like too many have, but God knows what I might have screwed up if I were in their places.  The wrongs anger me, but not really knowing if I would have done better is humbling.  As for forgiving Robert Strange; I must in order to be true to my beliefs, but I find his book a strange way to ask for forgiveness.  He might as well have said the Devil made him do it, and therefore doesn't need forgiveness, because he couldn't help himself.<br>
    Oh, und zince zis iss der krazee korner, let me assure you I'm shtill as krazee as der next guy.  &quot;Twas brillig and the slithy toves...&quot;
<p><code>-- gerald_ney@icpphil.navy.mil  (Gerald Ney, &quot;professor&quot;, 7/68-7/69) </code><p>


